21 DAYS BITCH!
be sorted @ nimbo.net

Today was really fun. I feel good because today I getting my lip pierced! Finally! Mom said I could and she's signed the forms and EVERYTHING! I'm so happy. I just found out that I have been accepted into Harvard. And Yale. I don't know which to choose... oh, why is life so hard sometimes? Last night I had to go and pay Joshua's bail. He's such a jerk. He got arrested for punching the Walmart clerk in the face for refusing to sell him beer. He's only 16! I want to tell the world that I love you all! You're all so special to me! I am making this journal friends only because I don't want the world to read what I'm writing, even though I'm posting it on the internet. Today, I got a digital camera! Yes! Here's ten thousand photographs of my cat. I want to say thanks to my dad for giving me my own computer and digital camera. Here's a photo of my room. The weather in Ontario is cold. I have nothing more to say. I went to the doctor yesterday, and he said I'm special!! And bipolar disorder. You should all do this quiz! It's amazingly accurate. You just put in your name and birthday, and it will tell you you're a moron. Dave's a bleep-ity bleep bleep. That's enough for now. But I'll leave you with this thought - sharing your life with strangers on the internet is the cheapest form of therapy available. Leave a comment and tell me I'm beautiful. Created with the Gregor's Semi-Automatic LiveJournal Updater™. Update your journal today!
Powered by Rum and Monkey Go ahead, update your LiveJournal. Or, make a different entry.

Yesterday was ok. Me, Melissa, my mom and dad went to church. I was happy cuz I got to see Mike<33! Then after we all went out to dinner at Buca di beppo. That food is great! And the whole place looks kewl. Whoever there decorates does a good job...and the whole place goes in like a circle - no windows though. 


I can't wait til Florida!!!!

Well...schools done for now. When my mom picked me up from the high school after the biology exam, she told me that she called Mrs. Foster and she said that I passed the math exam with a 66! Yea! Tomorrow I get to go to a birthday party...a party! I wanted to celebrate since I'm done with exams, but everybody was probably busy. I get to go to Florida for a week! I can't wait! I'll write some more later. I need to go buy Katie a present!

Tonight on some channel, these people are building this 2-floor airplane...in France!  Dude! That's like kewl!  I wanna go on it!  I think it might rain...it sure does look like it. Davey slept the whole day so I was bored in study hall, but he came after school to see some "people" and I guess I wasn't part of those "people". Ealier this afternoon, my new neighbor came over and he's like 10 and Carmel was out and he was like can I pet her? Me, the nice person said yea and he was like I've never petted a bunny before...I have a stuffed bunny though.  I was like o kewl. I actually cleaned my locker out yesterday and I found a lotta garbage...like in the top shelf and underneath all of my books at the bottom of my locker.  I need to put up some more pictures up so it'll look so prilly and I can see all of my distant friends that live so far away everyday (mostly everyday) and the cute boys that I love so much, like Kurt and Dave!  I need one of Matt K!  I have 2 but they won't fit in my locker.  It stinkys!  OMG!  It thundered! It's like really dark out for 7:04 pm!  Yup yup.  Me, Kerri, and John are homees/gangsters for life!  LOL! Well, I gg cuz there's this humungous black cloud over my house!  Bye!

School is great!  I actually love it....which is not unusual for me!  LOL!  Kerri's starting to like Matt again...but I still like him waaaaayyy more than anybody else probably does!  John is still going out with that ummm...I think her name is Ashley (opps!  I forgot her name and I sit with her at lunch!)  Wow...I was looking at them moods that you can chose...I never thought that they would have BITCHY for one of them!  LOL!  OMG!  Becca keeps babbling on about people I never met or heard of in my life...like her uncle that plays the guitar ::sarcastic:: and the other uncle that can pick her up...woopee...should I throw a party for your uncle and then Kevin...at the bus stop:  "Kevin this Kevin that"...SHUTUP!!  LOL!  Umm...no!  I know...I'm talking to myself!  LOL!  My cat, Pom Pom, has a MAJOR problem...at night he runs around the house like a squirrel on drugs!  Last night he ran into the fridge or something and it scared me and then tonight when I was calling my favoritest ex-boyfriend, Greg, he ran through the kitchen and balled the rug up and then he was trying to catch my foot!  It was weird! I caught Laura's cold...she finally told me...I got home Saturday and I fell asleep for about 2 hours then got some food, then fell back asleep for another 3 hours...then I woke up again and it was time to go to bed.  But Sunday I got out of going to church school...I was planning on going, but I didn't feel to good to go so my mom called me in sick!  Hopefully nobody missed me!  Then this Sunday (March 7th) I get to go to retreat and St Joe's or where ever from 2-8pm...man that's going to be very boring!  But we get to eat...I'm bringing a snack though! And know why that sucks...it costs $12!  RIP OFF!!!   Nobody's on...Matt and Dave were on earlier but not anymore and I miss them already! Does anybody like the song Yeah by Usher?  It's like the bestest one he's ever sang!  And it sounds great with Luda in it!  OOOO...want to know a few facts?  My mom's second cousin works for Colin Powell (secretary of state) and my cousin Keri who lives in Florida knows/met John Mayer through one of her friends that works for him or the record company!  I thought I would write that to spice this entry up a bit! How long are these things supposed to be anyways?  Well, I gotta go do something other than just sit on this uncomfortable chair and type in this thing!  LOL!  I'll update this thing as soon as I can or if I still remember the website or whatever!  Bub eye  ~*Angela*~
